        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 3 at 3:26AM CDT until June 3 at 4:15AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 326 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles southeast of
Groom, or 15 miles north of Clarendon, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 70 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect some tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile homes,
roofs, and outbuildings. People and animals outdoors will
be injured. Expect hail damage to roofs, siding, windows,
and vehicles.

Locations impacted include...
Howardwick, Lake Mcclellan, Lefors, Alanreed, Mclean, and Greenbelt
Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
